//Write a program to search an element and itâ€™s location in an array using pointer..

int main()
{
    int *p,a[10],n,i,count=0,num;
    printf("\n enter N:");
    scanf("%d",&n);
    p=a;
    for(i=0;i<n;i++)
    {
        printf("\n value at a[%d]:",i);
        scanf("%d",(p+i));
    }
    printf("\n enter the number to search:");
    scanf("%d",&num);
    for(i=0;i<n;i++)
    {
        if(num==*(p+i))
        {
            count++;
            printf("\n value found at a[%d]",i);
            break;
        }
    }
    if(count==0)
        printf("\n element not found");
}


Output:

enter N:6
 value at a[0]:4
 value at a[1]:7
 value at a[2]:2
 value at a[3]:9
 value at a[4]:5
 value at a[5]:1

 enter the number to search:2
 value found at a[2]


Reference:https://funcodepro.blogspot.com/2018/12/how-to-search-element-and-its-location.html
